By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Nasarawa State Governor, Engineer Abdullahi Sule, as a member of the Presidential Council on Digital Economy and E-governance. This was disclosed in a letter signed by the Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Professor Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami. Professor Pantami said the constitution of the presidential council is an effort to implement the National Digital Economy Policy (NDEPS) and the Nigerian E-governance Master Plan (NEGMP). The minister noted that Nasarawa State is critical to the success of Nigeria’s digital economy agenda. According to the statement, Governor Sule and other members of the council will be inaugurated by President Buhari, being the chairman of the council, at a later date. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja - Nasarawa State Governor, Engineer Abdullahi Sule, has said the state is ready and prepared to host its inaugural investment summit scheduled for tomorrow and next. Engineer Sule stated this on Tuesday, shortly after inspecting the Lafia airport ahead of the arrival of the former Ghanian… In "Top Stories" •Dr Isa Pantami, Minister of Communication and Digital Economy • BY JESSICA DOGO ABUJA - The Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Prof. Isa Pantami, has urged the board of the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC), to protect telecom consumers in the country. Pantami made the appeal when he inaugurated the… In "Technology" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -. Few weeks into the Presidential primaries of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), the immediate past Minister of Transportation and a top contender in the presidential race, Rt Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi has promised that he would grow the nation’s economy by revamping… In "Top Stories"